[![Coverage Status](https://coveralls.io/repos/dwagon/Hostinfo/badge.png)](https://coveralls.io/r/dwagon/Hostinfo)

Hostinfo is a set of tools for systems administrators to store and retrieve data about their servers.

What to do once you have hostinfo installed can be found in the docs/GettingStarted file

License information can be found in the docs/LICENSE file

Source code, documentation, updates, bug lists, etc can be found at https://github.com/dwagon/Hostinfo 

Hostinfo was released to open source by Interactive [http://www.interactive.com.au]
